  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="faq">
    <h3>Does responding to Google reviews help SEO?</h3>
    <p>Yes. Google has confirmed that responding to reviews signals that your business is actively managed, which is a local ranking factor. Businesses with high response rates consistently rank higher in Google Maps results.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq">
    <h3>How quickly should I respond to Google reviews?</h3>
    <p>Ideally within 24 hours. Faster responses signal to both Google and potential customers that your business is attentive and well-managed.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq">
    <h3>Should I include keywords in my Google review responses?</h3>
    <p>Yes, but naturally. Include your business type and location organically — such as "our restaurant in London" or "our dental clinic." Keyword stuffing looks robotic and hurts credibility.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq">
    <h3>Does the length of my review response matter for SEO?</h3>
    <p>Somewhat. Responses between 50 and 150 words tend to perform best — long enough to be genuine and include natural keywords, short enough to be readable and avoid looking like spam.</p>
  </div>
